Things are constantly changing. The breath, phases of the moon, the changing of the seasons. This can be both profound ‚Äî like watching a caterpillar transform into a butterfly ‚Äî and a grim reminder of the impermanence of all things. Even the body will eventually fail. 

It can be exceptionally challenging to welcome change and appreciate the natural unfolding of life as it is. 

When it comes to yoga and meditation, if we resist the changes that occur during practice, the old identity will try to hold on to the body as it is. Ergo, the body and mind becomes rigid, it tightens up, and the natural flow of energy slows down to a trickle or it may stop completely. 

Allow change to happen to you. Notice when there is resistance. Where do you feel stuck, stagnant, weighed down, heavy?

Just for today, practice being open and receptive to change. It could be something as simple as making a different choice for lunch or changing your hairstyle. Embracing the changes of the seasons can be fun. Try wearing earth tones for Fall. üçÇüçÅüçÇ 

Give yourself the room to expand, lighten, grow, shift. 

‚ÄúSome changes look negative on the surface but you will soon realize that space is being created in your life for something new to emerge.‚Äù - Eckhart Tolle

May you feel the joy born of gratitude. 
May you wake up to your own true beauty. 
May your worries be transformed into wonders. 
May your heart bloom with purpose. 
May you allow yourself to relax into peace. 
May you remember you are strong. 
May you know you are loved and cherished. 
May you know that I am grateful for you. 
