Time is such a weird concept. 
No matter what is happening in life each minute consists of 60 seconds. 
Each hour consists of 60 minutes; 3600 seconds. 
And each day 24 hours; 1440 minutes; 86,400 seconds.
But some days, that time feels as though it‚Äôs endless or no where near enough. 
Time feels different to each person, depending on what is happening in their life. 
It can move slow, it can move fast. 
There are days you feel no time has passed but it‚Äôs been hours. Or days when it feels as though hours should have passed and it‚Äôs been only minutes. 
Time always consists of the same measurements, the same increments, the same amount but feels different each day, to each person. 
Time is a weird concept. 
And right now, to me, it is moving faster than I feel it should. 
#ramblingsofkatiehope 
How does time feel to you, right now, in this moment?
